4c, in order
The blocker isn't XCI parsing — it's that Phase can't express XCI. {Header, Table, Data} hard-codes "one contiguous table at offset 0". XCI needs four collections at scattered offsets: magic at 0x100, root offset at 0x130, the root HFS0, then the secure HFS0 possibly gigabytes downstream past the update partition.
So: generalise the collector first, changing nothing observable. "Collect N bytes at absolute offset X, then run step S" — with PFS0's header and table becoming two steps. stream_container_test exists precisely to hold that refactor still. Then XCI is four more steps on top, emitting entries with absolute offsets straight into the gap-skipping feed_data that already works.
